H0.text: Which standard orchestral instrument has a name which derives from the French for high wood. Flute

H1.text: Which standard orchestral instrument has a name which derives from the French for high wood. Clarinet

H2.text: Which standard orchestral instrument has a name which derives from the French for high wood. Piccolo

H3.text: Which standard orchestral instrument has a name which derives from the French for high wood. Oboe

A4.text: The French word hautbois means 'high-pitched woodwind' in English.

A5.text: The spelling of oboe was adopted into English c. 1770 from the Italian oboè, a transliteration of the 17th-century pronunciation of the French name.
